---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const title = "About Me";
const description = "Learn more about the developer behind The Calm Developer blog.";
---

<BaseLayout title={title} description={description}>
	<article class="prose">
		<header>
			<h1>About Me</h1>
		</header>

		<section>
			<p>
				Hello! I'm a software engineer passionate about building clean, efficient, and user-centric applications. 
				With a focus on modern web technologies and a love for minimal design, I share my journey and 
				learnings through this blog.
			</p>
		</section>

		<section>
			<h2>My Expertise</h2>
			<ul>
				<li><strong>Frontend Development:</strong> React, Astro, TypeScript, and modern CSS.</li>
				<li><strong>Backend Systems:</strong> Node.js, Go, and PostgreSQL.</li>
				<li><strong>Cloud & DevOps:</strong> AWS, Docker, and CI/CD pipelines.</li>
				<li><strong>Software Architecture:</strong> Designing scalable and maintainable systems.</li>
			</ul>
		</section>

		<section>
			<h2>My Philosophy</h2>
			<p>
				I believe in the "calm developer" approach: writing code that is easy to read, simple to maintain, 
				and focused on solving real problems without unnecessary complexity. Great software isn't just about 
				the features—it's about the craftsmanship and the long-term health of the codebase.
			</p>
		</section>

		<section>
			<h2>Connect With Me</h2>
			<p>
				I'm always open to discussing new projects, interesting technologies, or just chatting about 
				software development in general.
			</p>
			<ul>
				<li><a href="https://github.com">GitHub</a></li>
				<li><a href="https://linkedin.com">LinkedIn</a></li>
				<li><a href="https://twitter.com">Twitter</a></li>
				<li><a href="mailto:hello@example.com">Email Me</a></li>
			</ul>
		</section>
	</article>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
	section {
		margin-bottom: 3rem;
	}

	h2 {
		border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
		padding-bottom: 0.5rem;
		margin-top: 3rem;
	}

	ul {
		list-style-type: none;
		padding-left: 0;
	}

	ul li {
		margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
		position: relative;
		padding-left: 1.5rem;
	}

	ul li::before {
		content: "→";
		position: absolute;
		left: 0;
		color: var(--link);
	}
</style>
